flowchart LR
  accTitle: The Ring of Fire family tree
  accDescr: Five handgun companies trace back to Raven Arms, founded by George Jennings in 1970. Lorcin Engineering was founded by Jim Waldorf in 1989; Davis Industries by George's daughter Gail and her husband Jim Davis in 1982; Phoenix Arms succeeded Raven after a 1991 fire; Bryco Arms descends from Jennings Firearms, founded by Bruce Jennings in 1978, by way of Calwestco; and Sundance Industries by George's nephew in 1989. 1992 production totals Bryco 204883, Davis 187779, Lorcin 187761, Phoenix 67824, Sundance 17757.
  R["Raven Arms<br/>George Jennings, 1970"]
  R --> Lm["Lorcin Engineering<br/>Jim Waldorf, 1989"] --> Lg["Lorcin Engineering<br/>187,761 guns in 1992"]
  R --> Dm["Davis Industries<br/>Gail and Jim Davis, 1982"] --> Dg["Davis Industries<br/>187,779 guns in 1992"]
  R --> FIRE(["Raven destroyed by fire, 1991"]) --> Pg["Phoenix Arms<br/>67,824 guns in 1992"]
  R --> Jm["Jennings Firearms<br/>Bruce Jennings, 1978"] --> CAL(["replaced by Calwestco, 1985-1990"]) --> Bg["Bryco Arms<br/>204,883 guns in 1992"]
  R --> Sm["Sundance Industries<br/>George's nephew, 1989"] --> Sg["Sundance Industries<br/>17,757 guns in 1992"]
  %% NOTE: classDefs deliberately set NO `color:` — under flowchart htmlLabels:false,
  %% a per-class color property makes multi-row label text render invisibly (a Mermaid 11
  %% rendering bug), so label color is left to the theme default (dark #1a1a1a). The origin
  %% node is distinguished by a pale-red fill + thick accent border, keeping dark text legible.
  %% Layout mirrors the original Figure 1-1: an origin box (Raven), a middle column of
  %% "origin company" rectangles (name + founder/year), and a right column of "became"
  %% rectangles (final company name + 1992 production). The two transitional events sit
  %% between the columns as ovals (stadium nodes). Phoenix has no middle box — Raven leads
  %% to it through the fire event, exactly as in the scan.
  %% CRITICAL: do NOT name a classDef `root`. Mermaid wraps the whole graph in
  %% `<g class="root">`, so a classDef called `root` emits `.root path{fill:...!important}`
  %% that paints EVERY edge path (which live inside that wrapper) with the node fill — it
  %% reads as a pale "shadow" wedge under each diagonal arrow. The origin node uses `origin`.
  classDef note fill:#f6f4f1,stroke:#7a1f1f,stroke-width:2px;
  classDef firm fill:#ffffff,stroke:#333333,stroke-width:1px;
  classDef origin fill:#fbeaea,stroke:#7a1f1f,stroke-width:3px;
  class R origin;
  class Lm,Dm,Jm,Sm,Lg,Dg,Pg,Bg,Sg firm;
  class FIRE,CAL note;
